description:
You are a Security Manager performing a quarterly system health diagnostic of your Nx Witness VMS installation. Programmatically query the VMS REST API at https://localhost:7001 (self-signed SSL; disable verification) using the 'admin' account (password: 'Admin1234!') to compile a comprehensive diagnostic report. Authentication is handled via bearer tokens obtained from the /rest/v1/login/sessions endpoint.

The report must be saved to ~/reports/system_health_report.json in pretty-printed JSON format (2-space indentation) with the following structure:

{
  "report_metadata": {
    "generated_at": "<ISO 8601 timestamp>",
    "report_type": "system_health_diagnostic",
    "system_name": "<systemName from /rest/v1/system/info>"
  },
  "server_info": {
    "servers": [ <array of server objects from /rest/v1/servers, each with at least id, name, version, status> ]
  },
  "cameras": {
    "devices": [ <array of device objects from /rest/v1/devices, each with at least id, name, status, model, vendor> ],
    "summary": {
      "total_count": <integer>,
      "online_count": <integer - devices with status 'Online'>,
      "offline_count": <integer - devices not 'Online'>
    }
  },
  "users": {
    "accounts": [ <array of user objects from /rest/v1/users, each with at least id, name, email, fullName, isEnabled> ],
    "summary": {
      "total_count": <integer>
    }
  },
  "storage": {
    "locations": [ <array of storage objects from /rest/v1/storages> ]
  },
  "system_settings": { <object containing settings from /rest/v1/system/settings> }
}

